SIMPLE: expunge
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expunge
<hw>Ex*punge"</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦ucr⟧nj")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Expunged</conjf>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦ucr⟧njd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Expunging</conjf> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦ucr⟧n"j⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[L. <ets>expungere</ets>, <ets>expunctum</ets>, prick out, expunge,
settle an account, execute; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>pungere</ets> to
prick, puncture. See <er>Pungent.</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To blot
out, as with pen; to rub out; to efface designedly; to obliterate; to
strike out wholly; <as>as, to <ex>expunge</ex> words, lines, or
sentences</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To strike out; to wipe out or destroy; to
annihilate; <as>as, to <ex>expunge</ex> an offense</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Sandys.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Expunge</qex> the whole, or lop th' excrescent parts.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To efface; erase; obliterate; strike out;
destroy; annihilate; cancel.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>expunging</ent>⟦br⟧
